@@ -0,0 +1,117 @@
+# Migration Guide: Dialog System Update
+
+## Overview
+
+This document outlines the changes made to the dialog system and how to migrate from the old enum-based approach to the new component-based approach for improved type safety and flexibility.
+
+## Key Changes
+
+### 1. Dialog Provider Updates
+
+The `DialogProvider` now supports two approaches:
+- **New Approach**: Pass components directly to `openDialog` and `openDrawer`
+- **Legacy Approach**: Continue using the enum-based system (backward compatible)
+
+### 2. Updated Context Interface
+
+The `DialogContextProps` interface now provides two methods for each dialog type:
+- `openDialog` / `openDrawer`: New component-based approach
+- `openDialogLegacy` / `openDrawerLegacy`: Legacy enum-based approach (for backward compatibility)
+
+## Migration Steps
+
+### For Dialogs
+
+#### Old way (Enum-based):
+```typescript
+openDialog('EDIT_WORKSPACE_NAME', {
+  title: 'Edit Workspace Name',
+  payload: { workspaceId: '123' },
+  props: { maxWidth: 'sm' }
+});
+```
+
+#### New way (Component-based):
+```typescript
+import EditWorkspaceNameForm from '@/components/home/EditWorkspaceNameForm';
+
+openDialog(EditWorkspaceNameForm, {
+  title: 'Edit Workspace Name',
+  payload: { workspaceId: '123' },
+  props: { maxWidth: 'sm' }
+});
+```
+
+### For Drawers
+
+#### Old way (Enum-based):
+```typescript
+openDrawer('EDIT_USER', {
+  title: 'Edit User',
+  payload: { userId: '123' },
+  props: { maxWidth: 'md' }
+});
+```
+
+#### New way (Component-based):
+```typescript
+import EditUserForm from '@/components/users/EditUserForm';
+
+openDrawer(EditUserForm, {
+  title: 'Edit User',
+  payload: { userId: '123' },
+  props: { maxWidth: 'md' }
+});
+```
+
+## Benefits of the New Approach
+
+1. **Type Safety**: Better TypeScript support for component props
+2. **Flexibility**: Any component can be used in dialogs and drawers
+3. **Reduced Boilerplate**: No need to maintain a large switch statement for dialog types
+4. **Maintainability**: Easier to add new dialogs without modifying the provider
+
+## Backward Compatibility
+
+The legacy methods (`openDialogLegacy` and `openDrawerLegacy`) are kept for backward compatibility. You can gradually migrate your codebase to the new approach over time.
+
+## Example Migration
+
+### Before:
+```typescript
+// In a component
+const { openDialog } = useContext(DialogContext);
+
+const handleEditWorkspace = () => {
+  openDialog('EDIT_WORKSPACE_NAME', {
+    title: 'Edit Workspace Name',
+    payload: { workspaceId: '123' },
+    props: { maxWidth: 'sm' }
+  });
+};
+```
+
+### After:
+```typescript
+// In a component
+import EditWorkspaceNameForm from '@/components/home/EditWorkspaceNameForm';
+import { useContext } from 'react';
+import { DialogContext } from '@/components/common/DialogProvider/DialogContext';
+
+const { openDialog } = useContext(DialogContext);
+
+const handleEditWorkspace = () => {
+  openDialog(EditWorkspaceNameForm, {
+    title: 'Edit Workspace Name',
+    payload: { workspaceId: '123' },
+    props: { maxWidth: 'sm' }
+  });
+};
+```
+
+## Notes
+
+1. All existing usages of `openDialog` and `openDrawer` with enum types will continue to work
+2. The new component-based approach provides better type checking and is more flexible
+3. Consider migrating to the new approach for new features
+4. Existing code can remain unchanged for backward compatibility
